# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback. Real files in the upload manifest
# (artifacts/*.html, sitemap.xml, issue plates) are served before this
# rule applies, so only unmatched paths fall through to the app shell.
# Destination is the bare root, not /index.html — Cloudflare's own
# documented 200-status "Proxying" examples target a path, not a
# filename, and /index.html directly 308s (its own HTML-normalization
# redirect), which can prevent the fallback resolving to a final 200.
/* / 200
